So here's to an exciting night.

231
00:18:58.800 --> 00:18:59.960 line:80%
Enjoy your meal.

232
00:19:07.520 --> 00:19:09.160 line:80%
I know you don't like seafood,

233
00:19:10.360 --> 00:19:12.560 line:80%
but you need protein
for what's planned later.

234
00:19:14.200 --> 00:19:15.680 line:80%
What do we have planned tonight?

235
00:19:49.240 --> 00:19:50.240 line:80%
I am sorry.

236
00:19:52.000 --> 00:19:52.840 line:80%
So sorry.

237
00:19:55.360 --> 00:19:57.160 line:80%
Have you stopped taking your pills?

238
00:19:58.360 --> 00:19:59.520 line:80%
Damn it, Klara.

239
00:20:00.160 --> 00:20:03.000 line:80%
Do I need to have you admitted
to the clinic again?

240
00:20:03.080 --> 00:20:05.000 line:80%
-Martin, I'm fine.
-I'm warning you.

241
00:20:05.520 --> 00:20:08.120 line:80%
I won't let Amelie have
a mentally deranged mother.

242
00:20:08.200 --> 00:20:11.520 line:80%
-I can't stomach the pills.
-The doctor can prescribe something else.

243
00:20:14.440 --> 00:20:16.160 line:80%
-Forgive me.
-So...

244
00:20:20.480 --> 00:20:21.560 line:80%
Time to eat.

245
00:20:39.640 --> 00:20:41.280 line:80%
How long is the babysitter staying?

246
00:20:47.200 --> 00:20:48.920 line:80%
Vigo will stay until we get home.

247
00:21:44.080 --> 00:21:45.240 line:80%
Give me your phone.

248
00:22:20.960 --> 00:22:22.760 line:80%
Welcome to our VP Night.

249
00:22:24.160 --> 00:22:26.600 line:80%
I'm here for you,
whatever you might desire.

250
00:22:26.680 --> 00:22:28.240 line:80%
What's a VP Night?

251
00:22:31.640 --> 00:22:32.960 line:80%
Very exclusive.

252
00:23:18.760 --> 00:23:20.520 line:80%
Martin, please. I'd like to go.

253
00:23:21.160 --> 00:23:22.840 line:80%
You haven't even finished your drink.

254
00:23:40.800 --> 00:23:44.320 line:80%
What's the matter? These women are
being paid very well for their services.

255
00:23:44.400 --> 00:23:46.760 line:80%
The entrance fee is donated
to the Children's Foundation.

256
00:23:46.840 --> 00:23:47.920 line:80%
It's a good thing.

257
00:23:49.720 --> 00:23:52.200 line:80%
Martin, please.

258
00:23:52.920 --> 00:23:54.280 line:80%
It's for a good cause.

259
00:23:59.200 --> 00:24:01.760 line:80%
He must have put something
in the champagne.

260
00:24:04.840 --> 00:24:05.800 line:80%
That's horrible.

261
00:24:07.560 --> 00:24:09.960 line:80%
I only regained consciousness
because of the pain.

262
00:24:31.160 --> 00:24:32.600 line:80%
Martin, please...

263
00:24:46.240 --> 00:24:48.680 line:80%
Klara, you must leave your husband.

264
00:24:49.240 --> 00:24:50.080 line:80%
Yes.

265
00:24:51.320 --> 00:24:54.080 line:80%
I should have done it
a long time ago. It's just...

266
00:24:54.600 --> 00:24:57.320 line:80%
I don't want Amelie to find out
what he's done to me.

267
00:24:58.360 --> 00:25:00.680 line:80%
That's understandable.
You didn't want to hurt her...

268
00:25:02.960 --> 00:25:05.680 line:80%
-How old is your daughter?
-Amelie is six.

269
00:25:05.760 --> 00:25:08.240 line:80%
I have a daughter, too.
Her name is Fabienne.

270
00:25:09.400 --> 00:25:10.880 line:80%
She's six, too.

271
00:25:12.000 --> 00:25:14.200 line:80%
-Where is your daughter now?
-She's asleep.

272
00:25:15.160 --> 00:25:17.560 line:80%
And who's looking after her? Is she alone?

273
00:25:18.200 --> 00:25:19.040 line:80%
Of course not.

274
00:25:20.000 --> 00:25:21.320 line:80%
We've got a babysitter.

275
00:25:22.760 --> 00:25:25.040 line:80%
Can you believe that he's a good father?

276
00:25:26.280 --> 00:25:28.000 line:80%
It's hard to believe, but it's true.

277
00:25:29.280 --> 00:25:30.720 line:80%
Amelie loves him.

278
00:25:33.240 --> 00:25:35.320 line:80%
I have to go, now, before he finds me.

279
00:25:35.400 --> 00:25:36.360 line:80%
Where are you?

280
00:25:39.160 --> 00:25:40.960 line:80%
You are closing a garage door.

281
00:25:41.040 --> 00:25:45.080 line:80%
You opened a car door.
What are you planning?

282
00:25:45.160 --> 00:25:47.520 line:80%
For what I'm planning to do,
it's better if I'm alone.

283
00:25:47.600 --> 00:25:48.480 line:80%
No.

284
00:25:48.560 --> 00:25:50.200 line:80%
No, don't do that.

285
00:25:51.080 --> 00:25:52.440 line:80%
Please don't do it.

286
00:25:52.520 --> 00:25:53.880 line:80%
Don't tell me what to do.

287
00:25:55.400 --> 00:25:56.520 line:80%
I'm sorry.

288
00:25:57.280 --> 00:26:00.480 line:80%
I'm so sorry, but you cannot do this.

289
00:26:02.720 --> 00:26:04.360 line:80%
Don't do this! Don't do this, please!

290
00:26:04.920 --> 00:26:06.040 line:80%
I am begging you.

291
00:26:06.160 --> 00:26:08.360 line:80%
Klara! Klara, please!

292
00:26:08.440 --> 00:26:10.640 line:80%
MARTIN - I always know where you are!
Brace yourself!

293
00:26:10.720 --> 00:26:13.920 line:80%
Either the Calendar Killer
or Martin will kill me.

294
00:26:14.000 --> 00:26:15.560 line:80%
So I'd rather do it myself.

295
00:26:17.880 --> 00:26:19.000 line:80%
If you do this...

296
00:26:21.000 --> 00:26:22.720 line:80%
Amelie will never get over it.

297
00:26:22.800 --> 00:26:23.640 line:80%
Believe me.

298
00:26:25.720 --> 00:26:27.840 line:80%
I can hear that you're not driving.

299
00:26:32.720 --> 00:26:36.320 line:80%
I am begging you. Please stop.
We'll find a way.

300
00:26:36.960 --> 00:26:38.240 line:80%
Klara?

301
00:26:39.080 --> 00:26:40.760 line:80%
Hello? Klara, please.

302
00:27:12.160 --> 00:27:13.360 line:80%
Enough!

303
00:27:13.440 --> 00:27:15.200 line:80%
I don't want to have
to take her to the ER.

304
00:27:15.280 --> 00:27:17.360 line:80%
I don't want to have
to take her to the ER.

305
00:27:33.440 --> 00:27:35.240 line:80%
You did well, darling.

306
00:27:35.960 --> 00:27:37.720 line:80%
Let's take a little break, okay?

307
00:27:39.240 --> 00:27:40.640 line:80%
Please take care of my wife.

308
00:27:47.600 --> 00:27:50.480 line:80%
Come. I'll show you to our powder room.

309
00:28:13.160 --> 00:28:15.080 line:80%
I'll go get you a stronger painkiller.

310
00:28:35.240 --> 00:28:36.320 line:80%
Did your wife enjoy it?

311
00:28:37.400 --> 00:28:38.800 line:80%
You never forget the first time.

312
00:28:38.880 --> 00:28:40.040 line:80%
Excuse me, please.

313
00:28:44.160 --> 00:28:47.440 line:80%
-Where's my wife?
-She must still be in the powder room.

314
00:29:43.960 --> 00:29:47.640 line:80%
Yo, this is Vigo. Feel free to leave
a message after the beep.

315
00:29:48.480 --> 00:29:49.720 line:80%
Hi, Vigo.

316
00:29:54.120 --> 00:29:55.640 line:80%
This message is for Amelie.

317
00:29:58.680 --> 00:29:59.800 line:80%
Hi, sweetie.

318
00:30:03.120 --> 00:30:04.320 line:80%
Mommy!

319
00:30:04.400 --> 00:30:06.560 line:80%
I just wanted to tell you
how much I love you.

320
00:30:11.080 --> 00:30:13.120 line:80%
It wasn't your fault, you hear me?

321
00:30:16.040 --> 00:30:17.400 line:80%
I love you so much.

322
00:30:30.400 --> 00:30:33.000 line:80%
CALLING

323
00:30:35.560 --> 00:30:37.320 line:80%
DAD
INCOMING CALL

324
00:30:45.560 --> 00:30:47.560 line:80%
I have no time right now. Call tomorrow.

325
00:30:47.640 --> 00:30:49.000 line:80%
How come? What's wrong?

326
00:30:49.080 --> 00:30:50.560 line:80%
-An emergency.
-An emergency?

327
00:30:50.640 --> 00:30:52.400 line:80%
I thought you were still on leave?

328
00:30:52.480 --> 00:30:55.920 line:80%
-I'm not at the emergency switchboard.
-So where are you?

329
00:30:56.000 --> 00:30:57.640 line:80%
Walk Me Home Helpline. Voluntary.

330
00:30:57.720 --> 00:30:59.880 line:80%
There's a woman who wants to kill herself.

331
00:30:59.960 --> 00:31:02.120 line:80%
Then call the police.

332
00:31:02.200 --> 00:31:03.560 line:80%
I don't know where she is.

333
00:31:04.320 --> 00:31:06.920 line:80%
-Maybe I can help you?
-That would be a first.

334
00:31:07.000 --> 00:31:09.600 line:80%
Tell me her name,
and I'll find out where she is.

335
00:31:09.680 --> 00:31:11.080 line:80%
No, I'm not allowed to.

336
00:31:11.160 --> 00:31:14.040 line:80%
Jules, you're talking to a woman
who wants to kill herself.

337
00:31:14.120 --> 00:31:15.960 line:80%
I can imagine what that's doing to you.

338
00:31:16.040 --> 00:31:18.480 line:80%
-You can?
-Yes. I can.

339
00:31:18.560 --> 00:31:19.640 line:80%
You want to save her,

340
00:31:19.720 --> 00:31:22.400 line:80%
-after the incident with Dajana--
-Stop it!

341
00:31:24.280 --> 00:31:26.680 line:80%
-Where are you?
-At home. Where else?

342
00:32:00.600 --> 00:32:01.560 line:80%
What?

343
00:32:01.640 --> 00:32:04.240 line:80%
Jules, I want to help you. Damn it.
I'm your father.

344
00:32:04.320 --> 00:32:07.760 line:80%
-Congrats on that realization.
-Tell me what you know.

345
00:32:09.000 --> 00:32:10.360 line:80%
So, what's her name?

346
00:32:12.880 --> 00:32:14.600 line:80%
All right. It's up to you.

347
00:32:14.680 --> 00:32:18.040 line:80%
-If it all goes wrong and you haven't--
-Her name is Klara.

348
00:32:18.920 --> 00:32:21.360 line:80%
-Klara... Klara what?
-Vernet.

349
00:32:21.440 --> 00:32:22.360 line:80%
That's it?

350
00:32:22.840 --> 00:32:24.440 line:80%
She was at the Le Zen Hotel today.

351
00:32:24.520 --> 00:32:26.960 line:80%
There must be
some secret pervert club there.

352
00:32:27.600 --> 00:32:28.880 line:80%
That's news to me.

353
00:32:29.600 --> 00:32:33.280 line:80%
But I'll ask around.
I still know someone there.

354
00:32:33.880 --> 00:32:36.040 line:80%
Stay out of everything else, okay?

355
00:33:56.480 --> 00:33:58.960 line:80%
Further snow showers
are expected in Berlin tonight.

356
00:33:59.040 --> 00:34:02.480 line:80%
So please drive carefully,
or make yourself comfortable at home.

357
00:34:03.280 --> 00:34:06.520 line:80%
It's 10:03 p.m.
The next news will be at 11:00 p.m.

358
00:34:18.800 --> 00:34:20.680 line:80%
Thank God. How are you feeling?

359
00:34:20.760 --> 00:34:21.800 line:80%
Shitty.

360
00:34:22.560 --> 00:34:24.040 line:80%
I feel sick. I threw up.

361
00:34:24.760 --> 00:34:27.400 line:80%
I can't go on. I am so tired.

362
00:34:28.560 --> 00:34:29.960 line:80%
Where are you now?

363
00:34:30.040 --> 00:34:32.240 line:80%
Where the Calendar Killer
will never find me...

364
00:34:32.680 --> 00:34:34.520 line:80%
Why is this so important to you?

365
00:34:34.600 --> 00:34:36.800 line:80%
Why can't you just leave me alone?

366
00:34:37.760 --> 00:34:40.280 line:80%
I'm sure you can't imagine it, but...

367
00:34:42.040 --> 00:34:44.080 line:80%
I know exactly what you're going through.

368
00:34:45.360 --> 00:34:47.880 line:80%
I've been on the phone
with women like you for a long time.

369
00:34:47.960 --> 00:34:52.120 line:80%
Women who were crying because their men
had beaten them half to death.

370
00:34:54.320 --> 00:34:55.880 line:80%
And were you able to help them?

371
00:34:56.520 --> 00:34:57.720 line:80%
I tried.

372
00:34:58.160 --> 00:34:59.200 line:80%
Over and over again.

373
00:34:59.840 --> 00:35:02.040 line:80%
But as soon as the police arrived,

374
00:35:03.040 --> 00:35:06.240 line:80%
suddenly everything was only half as bad,
and the men got away with it.

375
00:35:07.400 --> 00:35:08.720 line:80%
I don't understand it.

376
00:35:09.440 --> 00:35:11.680 line:80%
Why do women put up with it?

377
00:35:12.720 --> 00:35:14.640 line:80%
Because they're financially dependent.

378
00:35:16.760 --> 00:35:19.000 line:80%
Or they don't want
to take the kids from their dad.

379
00:35:20.880 --> 00:35:22.120 line:80%
Because they're ashamed.

380
00:35:23.560 --> 00:35:25.200 line:80%
Because they don't know where to go.

381
00:35:26.160 --> 00:35:28.480 line:80%
Or they think
they're to blame for the beatings.

382
00:35:29.360 --> 00:35:33.280 line:80%
Because they're terrified it'll only
get worse, and they'll be killed.

383
00:35:35.600 --> 00:35:39.080 line:80%
Or the husband has some hold
over the woman and is blackmailing her.

384
00:35:42.000 --> 00:35:46.440 line:80%
Klara, put an end to this misery,
but don't end your life.

385
00:35:46.520 --> 00:35:49.160 line:80%
Why is it so important to you?
You don't know me at all.

386
00:35:50.520 --> 00:35:53.240 line:80%
I told you about my daughter. Fabienne?

387
00:35:55.480 --> 00:35:56.520 line:80%
Yes.

388
00:35:58.400 --> 00:36:00.080 line:80%
Her mother killed herself.

389
00:36:00.680 --> 00:36:02.680 line:80%
Ever since that,
Fabienne hasn't been doing--

390
00:36:02.760 --> 00:36:04.280 line:80%
Why are you telling me all this?

391
00:36:05.120 --> 00:36:06.680 line:80%
To make me feel guilty?

392
00:36:08.240 --> 00:36:09.440 line:80%
No.

393
00:36:09.520 --> 00:36:11.440 line:80%
Her mother was in a clinic.

394
00:36:13.600 --> 00:36:15.680 line:80%
At first, it seemed things would be okay.

395
00:36:17.560 --> 00:36:19.160 line:80%
The doctors at Berger Hof...

396
00:36:19.240 --> 00:36:21.520 line:80%
-That was the clinic she was in.
-Berger Hof?

397
00:36:22.040 --> 00:36:24.640 line:80%
-I was there, too.
-What? What for?

398
00:36:26.280 --> 00:36:27.840 line:80%
Dissociative disorders.

399
00:36:30.320 --> 00:36:32.920 line:80%
Sometimes, I see things that aren't there.

400
00:36:34.000 --> 00:36:37.000 line:80%
-Were they able to help you?
-Yes, they did.

401
00:36:38.400 --> 00:36:40.200 line:80%
But I have to take medication.

402
00:36:40.720 --> 00:36:44.240 line:80%
And Martin threatens to have me
admitted again for every little thing.

403
00:36:48.440 --> 00:36:50.360 line:80%
Dajana suffered from severe depression.

404
00:36:53.040 --> 00:36:55.920 line:80%
I had hoped that they would
be able to help her, but...

405
00:36:56.920 --> 00:36:58.480 line:80%
It was too late.

406
00:37:02.360 --> 00:37:04.560 line:80%
You're not the only one
who's been through hell.

407
00:37:15.920 --> 00:37:18.360 line:80%
Mommy! Please open the door!

408
00:37:18.440 --> 00:37:19.640 line:80%
Mommy! It's on fire!

409
00:37:20.320 --> 00:37:21.840 line:80%
Mommy!

410
00:37:21.920 --> 00:37:24.560 line:80%
Mommy!

411
00:37:26.280 --> 00:37:27.280 line:80%
Mommy!

412
00:37:28.040 --> 00:37:29.520 line:80%
We can't get out!

413
00:37:36.520 --> 00:37:39.000 line:80%
Hurry, there's a fire,
and I hear someone screaming.

414
00:37:39.080 --> 00:37:40.160 line:80%
It's a child.

415
00:37:40.240 --> 00:37:42.520 line:80%
The firefighters will be there
in under two minutes.

416
00:37:42.600 --> 00:37:44.160 line:80%
Do not open the door!

417
00:37:44.240 --> 00:37:46.720 line:80%
It could cause a back draft,
and you'll be in flames.

418
00:37:46.800 --> 00:37:49.880 line:80%
-Please leave the building.
-But what about the kid? The screams...

419
00:37:49.960 --> 00:37:52.600 line:80%
My colleagues will take care of it.
Please get out of there.

420
00:37:52.680 --> 00:37:53.720 line:80%
Just a moment.

421
00:37:54.320 --> 00:37:56.520 line:80%
-Yes?
-Incident command vehicle 26. Stelling.

422
00:37:56.600 --> 00:37:58.680 line:80%
Tannberg, what's going on?
There's nothing here.

423
00:37:58.760 --> 00:38:01.440 line:80%
-What do you mean?
-There's no fire anywhere here.

424
00:38:01.520 --> 00:38:02.360 line:80%
Okay.

425
00:38:02.440 --> 00:38:04.080 line:80%
-Mr. Damelow?
-Yes? Where are you?

426
00:38:04.160 --> 00:38:06.000 line:80%
There's no fire
in Brandenburgische Street.

427
00:38:06.080 --> 00:38:06.960 line:80%
What?

428
00:38:07.040 --> 00:38:08.680 line:80%
-That prank will be expensive.
-Oh, God.

429
00:38:08.760 --> 00:38:11.120 line:80%
I was in a panic,
and I gave you the wrong address.

430
00:38:11.200 --> 00:38:12.600 line:80%
-Where are you?
-I am so sorry.

431
00:38:12.680 --> 00:38:15.240 line:80%
I'm at 24 Prince Regent Street.
Third floor.

432
00:38:16.520 --> 00:38:19.400 line:80%
-Please repeat that.
-24 Prince Regent Street. Hello?

433
00:38:35.040 --> 00:38:36.600 line:80%
Let me through! Damn it!

434
00:38:44.360 --> 00:38:45.640 line:80%
What happened?

435
00:39:22.440 --> 00:39:24.680 line:80%
Dajana locked up the kids in their rooms.

436
00:39:26.160 --> 00:39:29.640 line:80%
She wanted to spare them the sight
of their dead mother in the bathtub.

437
00:39:31.880 --> 00:39:34.920 line:80%
My little ones
tried desperately to get out.

438
00:39:37.000 --> 00:39:39.120 line:80%
Fabienne managed to hide in the closet.

439
00:39:40.080 --> 00:39:41.480 line:80%
She was taken to the hospital.

440
00:39:46.880 --> 00:39:51.120 line:80%
My son was probably playing
with a leftover birthday candle.

441
00:39:53.440 --> 00:39:55.400 line:80%
She must have noticed the smoke.

442
00:39:56.200 --> 00:39:57.400 line:80%
But it was too late.

443
00:40:00.280 --> 00:40:01.880 line:80%
She wanted to unlock the door.

444
00:40:04.400 --> 00:40:05.880 line:80%
But she had no strength left.

445
00:40:08.560 --> 00:40:09.840 line:80%
I am sorry.

446
00:40:33.160 --> 00:40:34.520 line:80%
Look at me.

447
00:40:53.120 --> 00:40:55.800 line:80%
Just a moment. I need to check something.

448
00:40:55.880 --> 00:40:57.000 line:80%
Stay on the line.

449
00:40:57.880 --> 00:40:58.720 line:80%
Turn around!

450
00:41:00.240 --> 00:41:01.520 line:80%
Come over here.

451
00:41:05.160 --> 00:41:06.480 line:80%
Show your face.

452
00:41:08.440 --> 00:41:09.280 line:80%
Klara!

453
00:41:11.280 --> 00:41:14.640 line:80%
12-06
HIM OR YOU

454
00:41:15.280 --> 00:41:16.880 line:80%
Look at me. Look at me.

455
00:41:20.480 --> 00:41:22.920 line:80%
Now... turn around.

456
00:41:27.640 --> 00:41:29.040 line:80%
Show me your face.

457
00:41:29.120 --> 00:41:31.400 line:80%
Klara! Look at me!

458
00:41:59.680 --> 00:42:02.320 line:80%
Look at me! Look at me!

459
00:42:02.400 --> 00:42:03.960 line:80%
Turn around.

