00:42:15.760 --> 00:42:17.520 line:80%
Now show me your face.

461
00:42:18.360 --> 00:42:19.600 line:80%
Klara!

462
00:42:19.680 --> 00:42:21.120 line:80%
Look at me!

463
00:42:24.040 --> 00:42:25.000 line:80%
Mommy?

464
00:43:52.000 --> 00:43:53.520 line:80%
Klara, I'm back.

465
00:43:53.600 --> 00:43:56.560 line:80%
Jules... he was here.

466
00:43:57.200 --> 00:43:58.440 line:80%
-He was here.
-Who?

467
00:43:58.880 --> 00:44:01.240 line:80%
The Calendar Killer.
He was here in the cabin.

468
00:44:03.960 --> 00:44:05.680 line:80%
Listen. This is what we'll do.

469
00:44:06.960 --> 00:44:09.480 line:80%
I'll send a cab to take you straight home.

470
00:44:09.560 --> 00:44:10.680 line:80%
Give me the address.

471
00:44:11.120 --> 00:44:12.280 line:80%
I'd rather take my car.

472
00:44:13.640 --> 00:44:14.640 line:80%
No, wait.

473
00:44:16.480 --> 00:44:17.520 line:80%
I'll send you something.

474
00:44:22.160 --> 00:44:24.640 line:80%
12-06
HIM OR YOU

475
00:44:37.520 --> 00:44:38.960 line:80%
Now they'll have to believe me.

476
00:44:40.040 --> 00:44:42.720 line:80%
The police and Martin.

477
00:44:51.600 --> 00:44:54.440 line:80%
He said it was
just another one of my delusions.

478
00:44:56.560 --> 00:45:00.400 line:80%
He asked how anyone would know
when I was in the parking garage.

479
00:45:02.080 --> 00:45:04.960 line:80%
Martin wanted to have me
readmitted to Berger Hof.

480
00:45:05.720 --> 00:45:08.080 line:80%
He has left you completely alone
with your fear.

481
00:45:09.800 --> 00:45:11.440 line:80%
The more I think about it...

482
00:45:15.080 --> 00:45:16.560 line:80%
the more I believe...

483
00:45:19.280 --> 00:45:21.080 line:80%
I believe that Martin's behind it all.

484
00:45:26.520 --> 00:45:27.760 line:80%
Why?

485
00:45:28.600 --> 00:45:30.960 line:80%
He's the only one
who always knows where I am.

486
00:45:32.000 --> 00:45:33.320 line:80%
He knows the cabin.

487
00:45:34.520 --> 00:45:35.800 line:80%
He's got the videos.

488
00:45:38.120 --> 00:45:40.080 line:80%
He's using my illness against me.

489
00:45:41.680 --> 00:45:43.120 line:80%
And on December 6...

490
00:45:44.560 --> 00:45:46.560 line:80%
We got married on December 6.

491
00:45:47.120 --> 00:45:49.560 line:80%
Please drive home right away
and get your child.

492
00:45:50.560 --> 00:45:52.200 line:80%
We'll meet in front of your apartment.

493
00:45:53.600 --> 00:45:54.800 line:80%
I'll help you.

494
00:45:58.480 --> 00:45:59.560 line:80%
You don't know him.

495
00:46:00.960 --> 00:46:02.080 line:80%
He always wins.

496
00:46:04.840 --> 00:46:05.920 line:80%
Not this time.

497
00:46:12.920 --> 00:46:13.960 line:80%
Jules.

498
00:46:18.760 --> 00:46:19.880 line:80%
He's here.

499
00:46:23.600 --> 00:46:24.800 line:80%
Klara, is someone there?

500
00:46:25.920 --> 00:46:27.760 line:80%
Klara, tell me what's happening?

501
00:46:38.080 --> 00:46:40.080 line:80%
Klara, is there someone in your house?

502
00:46:53.760 --> 00:46:55.880 line:80%
Can you hear me? Is someone there?

503
00:46:55.960 --> 00:46:58.040 line:80%
Can you hear me? Klara, please...

504
00:47:08.800 --> 00:47:10.360 line:80%
DECEMBER 6

505
00:49:27.920 --> 00:49:30.200 line:80%
-What?
-Is the woman still on the line?

506
00:49:31.200 --> 00:49:32.280 line:80%
Where are you?

507
00:49:33.640 --> 00:49:36.640 line:80%
I'm standing here in front of Le Zen.

508
00:49:36.720 --> 00:49:37.880 line:80%
And you?

509
00:49:37.960 --> 00:49:41.080 line:80%
-Did you find out anything?
-The manager was beside himself.

510
00:49:41.600 --> 00:49:43.080 line:80%
Obviously, he's going to deny it.

511
00:49:44.160 --> 00:49:46.120 line:80%
He would have told me. Trust me.

512
00:49:48.120 --> 00:49:52.000 line:80%
-Did you really look everywhere?
-Yes, there's nothing there.

513
00:49:54.160 --> 00:49:57.240 line:80%
Jules, do you hear me?
The woman lied to you.

514
00:49:59.880 --> 00:50:01.840 line:80%
Why should I believe you more than her?

515
00:50:02.920 --> 00:50:05.480 line:80%
-Given all the times you lied to Mom--
-The woman is lying.

516
00:50:06.280 --> 00:50:10.200 line:80%
And I swear to you.
Her suicide story doesn't add up.

517
00:50:21.600 --> 00:50:24.200 line:80%
NETWORK NOT AVAILABLE

518
00:50:47.960 --> 00:50:48.920 line:80%
Klara!

519
00:51:04.960 --> 00:51:08.960 line:80%
This is Klara Vernet's voicemail.
Please leave a message after the beep.

520
00:51:09.720 --> 00:51:13.720 line:80%
Klara, please call me back.
Please. I'm begging you.

521
00:52:04.320 --> 00:52:05.360 line:80%
Hey!

522
00:52:08.480 --> 00:52:10.600 line:80%
Calm down. Just calm down.

523
00:52:10.720 --> 00:52:11.600 line:80%
Hey, calm down.

524
00:52:12.600 --> 00:52:14.040 line:80%
Hey, calm down!

525
00:52:14.120 --> 00:52:15.320 line:80%
I won't hurt you.

526
00:52:16.720 --> 00:52:18.000 line:80%
Come on. I'll help you.

527
00:52:21.440 --> 00:52:22.840 line:80%
I'm Hendrik.

528
00:52:28.720 --> 00:52:30.000 line:80%
Come on. I'll help you.

529
00:52:35.320 --> 00:52:36.440 line:80%
Come on.

530
00:52:37.280 --> 00:52:38.160 line:80%
Come. It's alright.

531
00:53:26.000 --> 00:53:27.040 line:80%
Klara!

532
00:54:53.400 --> 00:54:54.440 line:80%
It's Hendrik, right?

533
00:54:55.760 --> 00:54:59.000 line:80%
Just let me out somewhere
when we get to the city.

534
00:54:59.720 --> 00:55:01.320 line:80%
It looks like you need a doctor.

535
00:55:02.400 --> 00:55:04.160 line:80%
I'll get you to the next ER.

536
00:55:06.280 --> 00:55:08.520 line:80%
It's nice that you're concerned.
But I'm fine.

537
00:55:08.600 --> 00:55:11.000 line:80%
Just let me out anywhere in the city.

538
00:55:13.000 --> 00:55:15.360 line:80%
NO NETWORK

539
00:55:34.600 --> 00:55:38.520 line:80%
How come you're driving around
at night in a Santa costume?

540
00:55:39.240 --> 00:55:40.480 line:80%
Bachelor's party.

541
00:55:42.240 --> 00:55:43.320 line:80%
I'm a stripper.

542
00:55:44.640 --> 00:55:46.200 line:80%
You should see my underpants.

543
00:55:46.680 --> 00:55:49.840 line:80%
Red with a white pom-pom
in front of the family jewels.

544
00:55:50.720 --> 00:55:52.440 line:80%
What? It pays the rent.

545
00:55:52.520 --> 00:55:54.360 line:80%
WALK ME HOME HELPLINE
3 MISSED CALLS

546
00:55:58.240 --> 00:55:59.720 line:80%
INCOMING CALL

547
00:56:01.960 --> 00:56:04.200 line:80%
Klara! Are you all right? What happened?

548
00:56:04.280 --> 00:56:05.280 line:80%
I saw him.

549
00:56:05.800 --> 00:56:07.840 line:80%
The Calendar Killer was in our cabin.

550
00:56:08.640 --> 00:56:09.720 line:80%
But I made it out.

551
00:56:09.800 --> 00:56:13.000 line:80%
-Where are you now?
-On my way to the city. I got a ride.

552
00:56:13.080 --> 00:56:15.000 line:80%
-Who with?
-Santa Claus.

553
00:56:15.800 --> 00:56:17.560 line:80%
-Excuse me?
-Don't worry about it.

554
00:56:19.160 --> 00:56:23.240 line:80%
Listen. Martin must be on his way home.
I have to get to Amelie before him.

555
00:56:23.320 --> 00:56:24.840 line:80%
Please be careful.

556
00:56:26.040 --> 00:56:28.600 line:80%
You shouldn't trust anyone tonight.

557
00:56:31.000 --> 00:56:32.440 line:80%
Daddy!

558
00:56:32.520 --> 00:56:34.840 line:80%
Please stay on the line.
I need to check on my daughter.

559
00:56:34.920 --> 00:56:36.520 line:80%
Mommy.

560
00:56:38.120 --> 00:56:38.960 line:80%
Daddy.

561
00:56:40.040 --> 00:56:41.360 line:80%
Is everything okay?

562
00:56:41.480 --> 00:56:43.160 line:80%
No. No, she is burning up.

563
00:56:44.240 --> 00:56:46.800 line:80%
I need to check if there's
any liquid fever medication left.

564
00:56:58.440 --> 00:56:59.800 line:80%
Mommy.

565
00:57:02.440 --> 00:57:04.000 line:80%
Mommy.

566
00:57:08.200 --> 00:57:09.640 line:80%
Daddy.

567
00:57:36.960 --> 00:57:38.640 line:80%
Mommy.

568
00:57:40.000 --> 00:57:41.240 line:80%
Can you sing?

569
00:57:42.520 --> 00:57:44.120 line:80%
-What?
-Sing?

570
00:57:46.800 --> 00:57:47.840 line:80%
Well...

571
00:57:50.800 --> 00:57:53.560 line:80%
Put the phone next to Fabienne's ear.

572
00:58:00.400 --> 00:58:05.160 line:80%
Behold, the moon has risen

573
00:58:07.000 --> 00:58:12.000 line:80%
The golden stars, they glisten

574
00:58:12.920 --> 00:58:17.080 line:80%
Upon the heavens bright

575
00:58:18.320 --> 00:58:23.480 line:80%
The forests rest in shadows

576
00:58:24.880 --> 00:58:30.160 line:80%
And from the quiet meadows

577
00:58:31.240 --> 00:58:36.400 line:80%
White haze rises into the night

578
00:58:44.680 --> 00:58:46.880 line:80%
Dajana used to
always sing that to Fabienne.

579
00:58:51.560 --> 00:58:52.960 line:80%
Is she calmer now?

580
00:58:56.760 --> 00:58:57.880 line:80%
Yes, she is.

581
00:58:58.600 --> 00:58:59.760 line:80%
Thank you.

582
00:59:03.720 --> 00:59:05.520 line:80%
I can't leave Amelie all alone.

583
00:59:08.680 --> 00:59:10.040 line:80%
I have to be there for her.

584
00:59:13.360 --> 00:59:15.000 line:80%
I mustn't destroy her life.

585
00:59:17.640 --> 00:59:19.920 line:80%
I've let that happen to me
all these years.

586
00:59:22.120 --> 00:59:23.240 line:80%
I loved Martin.

587
00:59:32.920 --> 00:59:34.240 line:80%
But I can't do it anymore.

588
00:59:37.320 --> 00:59:39.200 line:80%
I have to go home to my daughter...

589
00:59:40.080 --> 00:59:41.560 line:80%
and finally leave Martin.

590
00:59:42.320 --> 00:59:43.920 line:80%
I'll help you if you want.

591
00:59:46.640 --> 00:59:48.640 line:80%
I can make sure you and Amelie are safe.

592
00:59:50.040 --> 00:59:51.760 line:80%
Just tell me where you are and...

593
00:59:53.160 --> 00:59:55.680 line:80%
-I'll come.
-You've already helped me enough.

594
00:59:58.160 --> 00:59:59.600 line:80%
I have to do this alone.

595
01:00:02.840 --> 01:00:05.600 line:80%
And with the photo,
I have proof that the Calendar...

596
01:00:09.600 --> 01:00:12.760 line:80%
That I didn't just imagine it all.
Now they have to believe me.

597
01:00:16.400 --> 01:00:19.040 line:80%
Just another hour
and December 6 will be over.

598
01:00:22.640 --> 01:00:23.840 line:80%
My offer still stands.

599
01:00:25.280 --> 01:00:26.360 line:80%
Thank you, Jules.

600
01:00:29.240 --> 01:00:31.880 line:80%
My pleasure, Klara.

601
01:01:01.160 --> 01:01:02.280 line:80%
What was that all about?

602
01:01:02.880 --> 01:01:04.760 line:80%
The Calendar Killer is after you?

603
01:01:07.320 --> 01:01:08.560 line:80%
Can I get one of those?

604
01:01:10.040 --> 01:01:11.120 line:80%
Sure.

605
01:01:13.800 --> 01:01:16.680 line:80%
Another pack should be
in the box back there.

606
01:01:24.680 --> 01:01:26.080 line:80%
My first one in 15 years.

607
01:01:27.080 --> 01:01:28.520 line:80%
Do you have a light?

608
01:01:28.600 --> 01:01:29.680 line:80%
Where is it?

609
01:01:37.680 --> 01:01:40.360 line:80%
-Stop the car. Right now!
-Hey, calm down.

610
01:01:40.440 --> 01:01:42.040 line:80%
I always have the taser with me.

611
01:01:42.120 --> 01:01:43.920 line:80%
-Calm down!
-Open the door!

612
01:01:44.000 --> 01:01:46.120 line:80%
-Take it easy!
-Open!

613
01:01:46.200 --> 01:01:47.640 line:80%
I won't hurt you.

614
01:01:47.720 --> 01:01:48.880 line:80%
Okay?

615
01:01:48.960 --> 01:01:50.520 line:80%
Everything is fine. Really.

616
01:01:50.600 --> 01:01:52.000 line:80%
I'm not going to hurt you.

617
01:01:52.080 --> 01:01:53.400 line:80%
Hey, what...

618
01:02:04.840 --> 01:02:06.040 line:80%
Martin!

619
01:02:07.280 --> 01:02:08.400 line:80%
Stop it!

620
01:02:11.280 --> 01:02:13.040 line:80%
It wasn't nice of you to take off earlier.

621
01:02:13.120 --> 01:02:14.200 line:80%
Get in!

622
01:02:15.760 --> 01:02:18.200 line:80%
-We can't just leave him. He'll freeze!
-Get in. Now!

623
01:02:18.280 --> 01:02:19.240 line:80%
Let go!

624
01:02:39.000 --> 01:02:40.200 line:80%
I'm so sorry.

625
01:02:40.960 --> 01:02:41.920 line:80%
I'm so sorry.

626
01:03:09.320 --> 01:03:11.000 line:80%
You must have known I'd find you.

627
01:03:13.760 --> 01:03:14.840 line:80%
Who was that?

628
01:03:17.240 --> 01:03:18.920 line:80%
I saw footprints in front of the house.

629
01:03:20.320 --> 01:03:21.880 line:80%
Didn't you go into the bedroom?

630
01:03:23.320 --> 01:03:24.400 line:80%
The bedroom?

631
01:03:27.320 --> 01:03:28.320 line:80%
What's that?

632
01:03:29.120 --> 01:03:31.160 line:80%
A death threat from the Calendar Killer.

633
01:03:31.720 --> 01:03:33.160 line:80%
The Calendar Killer?

634
01:03:33.240 --> 01:03:34.960 line:80%
Klara, don't start with all that again.

635
01:03:43.840 --> 01:03:45.160 line:80%
I'll drive back there tomorrow.

636
01:03:45.240 --> 01:03:47.360 line:80%
If it's really written there,
I'll call the police.

637
01:03:48.520 --> 01:03:51.520 line:80%
But if you're just making it up again,
I'll take you back to Berger Hof.

638
01:03:56.680 --> 01:03:58.720 line:80%
I was in the garage. I saw the tube.

639
01:04:01.840 --> 01:04:03.120 line:80%
Don't ever do that again.

640
01:04:39.920 --> 01:04:41.000 line:80%
What are you doing?

641
01:04:41.520 --> 01:04:43.240 line:80%
I'm checking if Vigo texted me.

642
01:04:51.240 --> 01:04:52.520 line:80%
I was thinking about us.

643
01:04:55.880 --> 01:04:58.680 line:80%
Last year, after I took you
to the ER in Potsdam...

644
01:05:00.200 --> 01:05:02.320 line:80%
When we went back home
and I cooked for you,

645
01:05:02.400 --> 01:05:05.240 line:80%
you asked me for the thousandth time
why I don't get therapy.

646
01:05:07.240 --> 01:05:08.920 line:80%
The truth is, I started therapy.

647
01:05:10.320 --> 01:05:12.560 line:80%
But the guy just reeled off
the usual spiel.

648
01:05:12.640 --> 01:05:14.680 line:80%
How I lacked confidence

649
01:05:15.560 --> 01:05:18.560 line:80%
because I had an abusive father
and a mother who ran away.

650
01:05:18.640 --> 01:05:20.160 line:80%
I don't need a therapist for that.

651
01:05:24.960 --> 01:05:26.080 line:80%
You see?

652
01:05:27.280 --> 01:05:28.840 line:80%
I have no problem saying it.

653
01:05:30.720 --> 01:05:34.440 line:80%
If there was a self-help group like the AA
where you had to introduce yourself,

654
01:05:34.520 --> 01:05:35.360 line:80%
I'd do it.

655
01:05:35.440 --> 01:05:36.560 line:80%
I'd stand up and say,

656
01:05:37.160 --> 01:05:39.800 line:80%
"Hello. My name is Martin.
I'm 44 and I beat my wife."

657
01:05:40.520 --> 01:05:42.840 line:80%
And that's supposed to justify everything?

658
01:05:51.400 --> 01:05:53.280 line:80%
You need to stop provoking me, Klara.

659
01:05:56.000 --> 01:05:57.120 line:80%
Provoking you?

660
01:05:59.360 --> 01:06:00.640 line:80%
-I'm provoking you?
-Yes.

661
01:06:02.040 --> 01:06:03.280 line:80%
How?

662
01:06:07.120 --> 01:06:08.880 line:80%
Why didn't you leave a long time ago?

663
01:06:10.600 --> 01:06:14.600 line:80%
You just put up with it.
The beatings, the shouting.

664
01:06:19.880 --> 01:06:23.400 line:80%
You let it all happen, Klara.
Every punch, every kick.

665
01:06:26.120 --> 01:06:27.400 line:80%
Let it happen?

666
01:06:29.880 --> 01:06:31.240 line:80%
I let you...

667
01:06:33.320 --> 01:06:35.400 line:80%
drag me to that perverted club?

668
01:06:38.640 --> 01:06:40.280 line:80%
Let you offer me up...

669
01:06:41.240 --> 01:06:43.360 line:80%
to be whipped like a piece of meat?

670
01:06:46.480 --> 01:06:48.640 line:80%
-Are you serious?
-I didn't say that.

671
01:06:50.120 --> 01:06:52.520 line:80%
But you make me angry so often,
just by being there.

672
01:06:55.920 --> 01:06:58.520 line:80%
How can I respect you
if you don't even respect yourself?

673
01:07:00.520 --> 01:07:03.160 line:80%
You scare the shit out of me
every day, Martin.

674
01:07:04.720 --> 01:07:05.840 line:80%
I know.

675
01:07:07.480 --> 01:07:08.680 line:80%
And I'm sorry about that.

676
01:07:13.240 --> 01:07:14.400 line:80%
Do you believe me?

677
01:07:19.040 --> 01:07:21.000 line:80%
Do you believe that I love you?

678
01:07:26.560 --> 01:07:29.000 line:80%
I'll tell you something.
You won't leave me!

679
01:07:29.560 --> 01:07:30.920 line:80%
Do you understand me?

680
01:07:43.840 --> 01:07:45.040 line:80%
Drive me home.

681
01:07:46.560 --> 01:07:48.000 line:80%
I want to be with my daughter.

682
01:11:44.760 --> 01:11:46.040 line:80%
I can help you.

683
01:12:36.280 --> 01:12:37.280 line:80%
So...

684
01:12:38.000 --> 01:12:39.480 line:80%
brace yourself for what's coming.

685
01:12:42.560 --> 01:12:44.320 line:80%
You won't touch me in front of Amelie.

686
01:12:49.200 --> 01:12:50.800 line:80%
Don't tell me what to do.

687
01:13:01.400 --> 01:13:04.680 line:80%
Never touch me again.

688
01:13:15.600 --> 01:13:16.480 line:80%
Klara!

689
01:13:16.920 --> 01:13:17.760 line:80%
Klara!

690
01:13:49.240 --> 01:13:50.280 line:80%
Vigo?

691
01:14:02.160 --> 01:14:03.280 line:80%
Vigo?

692
01:14:18.400 --> 01:14:23.880 line:80%
Behold, the moon has risen

693
01:14:25.560 --> 01:14:31.040 line:80%
The golden stars, they glisten

694
01:14:32.440 --> 01:14:37.320 line:80%
Upon the heavens bright

695
01:14:37.880 --> 01:14:38.880 line:80%
Amelie?

696
01:14:40.400 --> 01:14:45.920 line:80%
The forests rest in shadows

697
01:14:47.120 --> 01:14:52.800 line:80%
And from the quiet meadows

