and looked the other way...

769
01:21:31.800 --> 01:21:32.800 line:80%
It broke her.

770
01:21:33.840 --> 01:21:38.080 line:80%
And when she took her own life,
she took my children's lives with her.

771
01:21:39.400 --> 01:21:41.480 line:80%
And she took mine, too.

772
01:21:46.000 --> 01:21:48.240 line:80%
I do what I do to give women like you

773
01:21:49.120 --> 01:21:51.040 line:80%
the chance to fight back.

774
01:21:52.960 --> 01:21:54.080 line:80%
One minute.

775
01:21:56.960 --> 01:21:58.040 line:80%
You can do it.

776
01:21:59.120 --> 01:22:00.320 line:80%
Think of Amelie.

777
01:22:01.280 --> 01:22:02.280 line:80%
She needs you.

778
01:22:03.280 --> 01:22:05.040 line:80%
But not a father like him.

779
01:22:20.080 --> 01:22:21.200 line:80%
I'm sorry.

780
01:22:26.960 --> 01:22:28.120 line:80%
Okay, please...

781
01:22:30.600 --> 01:22:31.960 line:80%
Be still.

782
01:22:35.480 --> 01:22:36.880 line:80%
